<br>
Now on to the other stuff, people that toss around buzzwords regarding networking are a danger to someone who might take them seriously that's genuinely trying to learn or asking for help. Code Red impacted very specific operating systems under very specific conditions. Spouting off about it just by name is akin to warning everyone about the &quot;Good times&quot; virus.<br>
<br>
By the way, the Cisco immediate fix was not a flash upgrade and they by no means &quot;took their phone off the hook.&quot; All it required was adding a few lines of code to a border router.<br>
Here's the link. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.cisco.com/warp/public/63/nbar_acl_codered.shtml">www.cisco.com/warp/public...ered.shtml</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Cisco has some of the best and fastest response to problems in the industry. They have to. There's too much competition for them to no be on the ball.<br>
<br>
<br>
Also, anyone using the hardware routers that have been mentioned thus far would be using RFC 1918 (private, nonroutable) IP space. There's really too much information in &quot;why&quot; they wouldn't have to worry about firewalls and such to post here, so here's a link to the RFC.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.cis.ohio-state.edu/cgi-bin/rfc/rfc1918.html">www.cis.ohio-state.edu/cg...c1918.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
<br>
The &quot;gigabit&quot; comment was actually a joke that I hoped you would get so you would see what I was talking about with the buzzwords. You spouted off about the IEEE ethernet specs. Well, gee, exactly &quot;which&quot; spec were you referring to? There are &quot;specs&quot; for everything from 2 meg thinnet,  gigabit ether/fibre, to wireless.<br>
In any case, your network bottleneck is not going to be your local lan segment. Odds are that anyone with a home lan is running 802.3 cat5 10 meg or cat 5 100 meg. This puts the bottleneck at your wide area (ISDN, DSL, Cable) since most people will be getting &quot;maybe&quot; T1 speed at 1.5 megs and last time I checked 1.5 was less than 10.<br>
<br>
So in summary, no I'm not an ass, yes I know what I'm talking about, and unless someone genuinely needs help in this thread I'm done with it.<br>
